BAN ALCOHOL
*Family problems.
*Violence.
*Un-lawful behavior.
*Poor work ethics.
*Lack of respect for the community.
*Lack of respect for them-self.
*A burden on the medical system and tax payer.
*Lost days of work and play, loss of memory.
*Fines
*Loss of income.
*Lack of promotion.
*Damage to your self and others, most mentally and physically.
*Criminal activity.
*Death
If your partner is a heavy drinker, you can expect all of the above.
If you are an alcoholic or heavy drinker or if the booze is in control of your life, you need to address that.
It's time to ban alcohol, it only causes problems and has no place in a modern society.
In this case, we need to see a very long jail term and restitution for the family.

RIP children.
Our hearts go-out to the families affected.
